snippet.textDisplay:
Next time you make Italian wedding soup, make the broth first and get the broth boiling. Then add your RAW meatballs and pasta. The meatballs will cook and add flavor to the broth and the starch in the pasta will add a thickness to the broth. When the meatballs are that small they sink and then when they’re fully cooked they float to the top.

Source: my mom is Italian and makes wedding soup for every occasion.
